<p>I'm trying to include a long string in an external file using the following syntax: </p>  <pre><code>&lt;fx:String id="myText" source="examples/text.txt" /&gt; </code></pre>  <p>But it's generating an error: </p>  <pre><code>1084: Syntax error: expecting identifier before rightparen.  </code></pre>  <p>Is there something I'm missing? </p>  <p>I've seen similar for embedding a text file using ActionScript but I would like to embed a string value using MXML. </p>  <p>I've found this example on <a href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/flex/using/WS2db454920e96a9e51e63e3d11c0bf69084-79cd.html" rel="nofollow">Flex help</a> docs:  </p>  <pre><code>&lt;fx:String id="myStringProperty1" source="./file"/&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I can't see anything that I'm doing differently. </p>